headline: Nike price target lowered to $90 from $91 at Goldman Sachs
summary: Goldman Sachs analyst Brooke Roach lowered the firm’s price target on Nike (NKE) to $90 from $91 and keeps a Buy rating on the shares. The firm is cutting its FY26 EPS view by 17c to $2.16 and its FY27 view by 15c to $2.92 to reflect updated FX, recent moderation in traffic trends across the industry in early 2025, and its expectation for weaker gross margins as a result of more persistent channel and product mix shift into FY26, the analyst tells investors in a research note.
